        "title": "Field @timestamp using Spring Data ElasticSearch",
        "body": "<p>What I am trying to achieve:<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>insert document in ElasticSearch using Reactive Spring Data ElasticSearch with a field <code>@timestamp<\/code> (note the &quot;at&quot; @ sign for timestamp, it is <code>@timestamp<\/code>, not just timestamp).<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>What I tried:<\/p>\n<pre><code>@Repository\npublic interface ElasticRepository extends ReactiveCrudRepository&lt;ElasticPojo, String&gt; {\n\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n<pre><code>@Document(indexName = &quot;theindex&quot;)\npublic class ElasticPojo {\n\n    @Field(type = FieldType.Date)\n    private long timestamp;\n\n    @Id\n    private String id;\n\n<\/code><\/pre>\n<p>Issue:<\/p>\n<p>This will insert a <code>timestamp<\/code> field inside ElasticSearch, not <code>@timestamp<\/code><\/p>\n<p>How to insert a field <code>@timestamp<\/code>?<\/p>\n",
